# Documentation and Changelog Baseline

- If behavior, contracts, or user-facing flows change, update documentation accordingly:
  - relevant READMEs,
  - API/contract docs,
  - database/schema docs (when applicable),
  - migration notes.
- Keep examples and referenced configurations in sync with the new behavior.
- For user-visible changes:
  - add or update changelog/release-note documentation when the repo has a convention.
- Include a “how to verify” note in the description of the change when automated validation is incomplete.

## Documentation Placeholder Commands

- Prefer running any configured documentation checks:
  - `DOCS_LINT_COMMAND`
  - `DOCS_BUILD_COMMAND`
  - optional `DOCS_LINK_CHECK_COMMAND`

